[1] Nigeria (Borno): fatal cases
Date: Fri 22 Mar 2019 19:19:18 WAT
Source: Xinhua News Agency [abridged, edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/africa/2019-03/22/c_137916026.htm


[Local authorities said on Fri 22 Mar 2019], 13 children have been confirmed killed following an outbreak of measles in Nigeria's northern state of Borno.

In a statement reaching Xinhua, the Borno State Primary Health Care Agency said the airborne disease has spread across 25 local council areas in the state.

The disease, a leading killer in developing countries like Nigeria, is showing a steady rise in Borno, with 4693 people already infected, the government agency said. "13 council areas are most affected by measles in 33 wards," the statement said.

On [Thu 21 Mar 2019], Babagana Abiso, a director of disease control in the state, said efforts were ongoing to contain the spread of the disease.

Abiso said due to the outbreak, 1.7 million kids are to be immunized against the disease.

The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) and the World Health Organization (WHO) would provide technical support for the 10-day immunization exercise, the official said.

"Immunization remains one of the most effective ways to protect children from killer diseases," he said, explaining that children of ages 6 months - 10 years are targeted for the immunization.

[Editor: xuxin]

