A further 5 people in Auckland have been diagnosed with the measles.

Auckland medical officer of health Dr William Rainger said the total number of cases in the region had risen to 9 but 4 of the 5 new cases were household contacts.

"There is one new case which isn't linked to an existing case, a woman in her 40s from Rodney," Rainger said.

He said the person was now in isolation, but she had been infectious since Mon 18 Mar 2019.

