[7] Macau: rise in cases
Date: Tue 26 Mar 2019
Source: Macaubusiness, Macau News Agency (MNA) [abridged, edited]
http://www.macaubusiness.com/cases-of-measles-rises-to-20/


The Health Bureau (SS) has confirmed in a release on [Tue 26 Mar 2019] that a 29-year-old worker in Kiang Wu Hospital has been infected with measles.

The man, who is from mainland China, was working as a ward assistant, and was found to be infected on [7 Mar 2019] when delivering a meal to a hospital ward.

As the man is from the Mainland, the SS does not know if he had received a measles vaccine. The man had developed a fever on [20 Mar 2019], and a rash on [23 Mar 2019]. However, records showed he had worked on [22 Mar 2019].

According to the data provided in the release, 8 employees of Kiang Wu Hospital have been found to be infected with measles since the 1st cases of measles were reported in early March [2019].

The health authority says that more than 250 medical staff in Macau have been re-vaccinated.

In addition, the release notes that a 26-year-old measles patient whose condition was previously reported has confirmed that he had accompanied his family to Kiang Wu Hospital on [6 Mar 2019] in the afternoon.

Although the 26-year-old had traveled to Thailand from [7-12 Mar 2019], the patient was categorised as an internal case, as he had contact with the 5th victim.

[Byline: Yi Wei Wong]

